# ecash mode - SPACER_MODE=ecash (the full ladder, doc 07 §9). Reads are snapshot-served (doc 15): the refresh_snapshots precondition reads arbiter/src/lnd.py (the LND wallet backs query_balance in this mode, and query_channels always) against the fake lncli at $LNCLI_BIN; eCash writes stop at the allowance / standing-approvals gates or the timing-layer acknowledgment (the fake suite never drains the queue) before any mint call - arbiter/src/ecash.py is imported only for the fund_ecash allowance gate (the exposure lookup and the gate-pass reservation, doc 07 §8) and no cashu subprocess ever runs (CASHU_BIN / CASHU_MINT_URL are deliberately unset; an unexpected arbiter-side mint call would error loudly). No live bitcoind / LND / mint traffic for any variant in the current manifest.
